snippet.textDisplay:
Originally this song is written by *'Amir Khusro' and he is considered as early writer of Hindi Literature* (that consist Brij, Awadhi). As area of his residence is around present *Upper Uttar Pradesh* it is natural that local words also written. Some says he also was the one who *originated Hindi Language* (Khadi Boli ~ खड़ी बोली).
And *parallely Urdu was originated* at that time... Those both languages came into existence around the same timeline ( *Sultanate Period/Medieval History* ), at same land... That is *Uttar Pradesh* North India. They both are newest in the history of World Languages.

(P.S. I'm a student of Hindi literature & History)

We may be separated as Nationals... But we can't ever separated by Our Culture... It is there right there ❤️ and always will be...
